g ordinary differential equations by using a trial step at the midpoint of =
an interval to cancel out lower-order error terms. The second-order formula=
 is k_1 =3D hf(x_n,y_n) (1)  k_2 =3D hf(x_n+1/2h,y_n+1/2k_1) (2)  y_(n+1) =
=3D y_n+k_2+O(h^3) (3)   (where O(x) is a Landau symbol), sometimes known a=
s RK2, and the fourth-order formula is k_1 =3D hf(x_n,y_n) (4)  k_2 =3D hf(=
x_n+1/2h,y_n+1/2k_1) (5)  k_3 =3D hf(x_n+1/2h,y_n+1/2k_2) (6)  k_4 =3D hf(x=
_n+h,y_n+k_3) (7)  y_(n+1)...">
